book.title: The Success of 7-Eleven Japan
book.intro: When analyzing 7-Eleven Japan's advanced and innovative management style, the authors of this study highlight the existence of the "integrated information system". This is because of the key role it plays not only in forming this firm's corporate strategy but also in developing its functional strategies for logistic support, merchandising and store operations. The authors explore the integrated information system, a symbol of the competitiveness of 7-Eleven Japan.
author: Akira Ishikawa
Tai Nejo
